Introduction¶

Author: Chao Li (cl1486)

Dataset: Crypto_quotes_with_change_label.csv

Features: various technical indicators including "EMA","MACD" and so on.

Label: the past one month quotes change, including "High position", "Middle" and "Low position"

EDA and data processing¶

data cleanning¶

In [41]:
# drop null value
ori_data = ori_data.dropna()

# get dummy varibables
dum_df = pd.get_dummies(ori_data, columns=[
                        'EMA-trend', 'MACD-position', 'MACD-indicator'], drop_first=True)

# label processing
le = preprocessing.LabelEncoder()
dum_df['Quotes_label'] = le.fit_transform(dum_df['Quotes_label'])

train-test split¶

In [42]:
X = dum_df.iloc[:, dum_df.columns != 'Quotes_label']
y = dum_df['Quotes_label']

# Train-test split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, random_state=0)

Random forest¶

Model training¶

In [43]:
clf = RandomForestClassifier(class_weight='balanced', random_state=0)
# the balanced means the large lag between the 1 and 0, e.g. only 2 of 1 but 998 of 0.
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
Out[43]:
RandomForestClassifier(class_weight='balanced', random_state=0)
In [44]:
trees = clf.estimators_[:9]

Visualization¶

In [45]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(60, 60))

for i in range(4):
    plt.subplot(2, 2, i+1)
    tree.plot_tree(trees[i], feature_names=X_train.columns,
                   class_names=le.classes_, filled=True)
    plt.title(f"Random Forest estimator {i+1}", fontsize=70)

plt.show()
fig.savefig("Random Forest.png")

Confusion matrix and evaluation¶

In [46]:
# make prediction
y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)

# print out prediction results
print('Report:\n')
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
print('Confusion Matrix:\n')
print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))

Feature importance¶

In [52]:
feature_names = X.columns

importances = clf.feature_importances_

forest_importances = pd.Series(importances, index=feature_names)
std = np.std([tree.feature_importances_ for tree in clf.estimators_], axis=0)


fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
forest_importances.plot.bar(yerr=std, ax=ax)
ax.set_title("Feature importances using MDI")
ax.set_ylabel("Mean decrease in impurity")
fig.tight_layout()

Model discussion and analysis¶

The overall predicting accuracy is not good enough. From the confusion matrix, the prediction on recognizing the middle position is bad. However, this model performs well in classifying the high position and low position.

After printing several estimators under the random forest, the tree structure of these estimators is not complex, where it conforms to the major ideal of random forest, using the simple tree to vote the final prediction.

One guessed the reason for the high prediction precision on the "High position" and "Low position" is that there is a distinct difference between each quote condition. For example, all the coin in the high position has a similar technical indicator.

The potential reason for the low accuracy on predicting the middle could be that since the "Middle" includes a lot of similar trends or signals to another two classes, where this may cause a confused prediction on the result.

Conclusion¶

This random forest result supports the application of using ML to predict or identify the market quotes.

This means that, some technical indicators are useful to help identify the position of the current quotes, according to the random forest result, such as "DEMA" and "HT_TrendLine". Especially, from the above result, "DEMA" is one of the most important technical indicators when recognizing the position of the current quotes.
